I enjoy the conversion process, but I can't pay $600 or more for the host receiver/barrel plus the nearly $300 for the correct parts.When you add the cost of a new Makarov plus about 75-80 dollars for a third magazine and 200 rounds of ammo, trading your old MAK for a new Makarov is a pretty good deal.The only requirement (besides a MAK 90 in good shape) is that the receiver be "square cut". I can't use an angle cut receiver for my project. If you're unsure what is meant by square cut, there are several YouTube videos that explain this. At the time of trade, the buttstock on your MAK will have to be off for me to confirm that it is a square cut receiver.Many thanks.
